The paper deals with the stability of exchanges in a network, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and social networks (cs.SOC). The use of preferences and payoffs suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of decision making (cs.DM) and economic theory (cs.EC). Finally, the mention of a generalized stable matching in the paper's existence proof suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of social choice (cs.SI).
